  String get diabetes => '1. Diabetes\n\nЁЯй║ What is Diabetes?\n\nтАв Diabetes is a long-term condition where your body has trouble using sugar (called glucose) from your food.\nтАв Normally, a hormone called insulin helps carry sugar from your blood into your bodyтАЩs cells for energy.\nтАв In diabetes, your body either doesn\'t make enough insulin or doesnтАЩt use it well, causing sugar to stay in your blood.\nтАв Too much sugar in the blood for a long time can harm your heart, kidneys, eyes, and nerves.\nтЪая╕П Common Symptoms (What People May Feel)\nтАв ЁЯе╡ Feeling very thirsty often: You may drink more water than usual and still feel dry.\nтАв ЁЯЪ╜ Frequent urination: You may go to the toilet more, especially at night.\nтАв ЁЯШ┤ Feeling tired all the time: You might feel sleepy or weak, even after resting.\nтАв ЁЯСА Blurry vision: Your eyesight might suddenly seem less clear.\nтАв тЪЦя╕П Losing weight without trying: This can happen even when you are eating well.\nтАв ЁЯй╣ Cuts that heal slowly: Small wounds or infections might take longer to get better.\nтАв ЁЯж╢ Numbness or tingling: You may feel pins and needles in your hands or feet.\nЁЯза Why It Matters\nтАв Diabetes doesn\'t always show symptoms early, but over time it can cause serious health issues.\nтАв It increases your risk for heart problems, kidney failure, eye damage, and nerve pain.\nтАв If not treated, it may even lead to stroke or limb damage (requiring amputation in extreme cases).\nтАв The good news: with lifestyle changes and care, it can be managed well.\nтЬЕ What You Can Do (Precautions and Home Care)\nЁЯН╜я╕П Eat Smarter\nтАв Avoid sugary snacks and soft drinks: These quickly raise your blood sugar.\nтАв Eat more vegetables, whole grains (like brown rice), and fresh fruits: They help control sugar levels.\nтАв Reduce oily and fried food: These can lead to weight gain and worsen blood sugar.\nтАв DonтАЩt skip meals: Eating at regular times helps maintain balanced sugar levels.\nЁЯПГ Stay Physically Active\nтАв Aim for at least 30 minutes of walking or light activity every day.\nтАв Simple activities like cleaning, playing with kids, or doing housework also help.\nтАв Physical movement helps your body use insulin better.\nЁЯУЙ Manage Your Weight\nтАв Even small weight loss (like 5тАУ10% of your body weight) can make a big difference in sugar control.\nтАв Obesity is a strong risk factor for type 2 diabetes.\nЁЯзк Monitor & Get Checked\nтАв Check your blood sugar if you are over 35, overweight, or if someone in your family has diabetes.\nтАв Early testing helps you take action before it becomes serious.\nЁЯЪн Say No To...\nтАв Smoking: It worsens blood flow and can damage your organs faster.\nтАв Alcohol: It can increase or suddenly drop blood sugar, both of which are dangerous.\nтАв Sugary drinks: Switch to water, buttermilk, or unsweetened tea.\nЁЯзШтАНтЩАя╕П Mental and Emotional Care\nтАв Diabetes can be stressful. You might feel anxious or frustrated about lifestyle changes.\nтАв Talk to someoneтАФfriends, family, or a counselor. You\'re not alone.\nтАв Stress itself can raise blood sugar, so keeping calm really helps.\nЁЯУМ When to See a Doctor\nтАв If you notice symptoms mentioned above, especially blurred vision, tiredness, or frequent urination.\nтАв If you have wounds that donтАЩt heal or numbness in hands/feet.\nтАв For regular sugar testingтАФeven if you feel okay.\n';
